<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING COMPRESSOR AND CLUTCH, TWO CYLINDER RECIPROCATING TYPE - After 01/01/1993 (R-134a) - REMOVE
        AND INSTALL - BASEPLATE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>BASEPLATE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the baseplate bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601719" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601719" filename="../figg16/G1601719.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 19. Remove Baseplate Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove baseplate and gasket. If the baseplate is stuck, lightly tap the edges of the
                    baseplate with a soft hammer.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove any gasket material adhering to the baseplate or crankcase. This should be done
                    in a manner such that the sealing surfaces are not scratched or nicked. Be sure to remove ALL gasket
                    material from the crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a thin film of mineral oil to a new gasket and the sealing surface of the
                    crankcase and baseplate.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Properly align the gasket on the crankcase (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601720">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601720" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601720" filename="../figg16/G1601720.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 20. Align Gasket On Crankcase</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the baseplate and bolts. Tighten baseplate bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601721">Figure 21</hotlnk>) to 10 to 16 ft-lbs. (13.6 to 21.7 N&#183;m) in
                    sequence given in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1601722">Figure 22</hotlnk>.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1601721" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601721" filename="../figg16/G1601721.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 21. Tighten Baseplate Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f1601722" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1601722" filename="../figg16/G1601722.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 22. Tighten In Proper Sequence</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
